This paper deals with off-policy evaluation and policy optimization, which are topics related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of value-functions and importance weights also suggests a focus on reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves statistical analysis and optimization, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the exploration aspect of the paper suggests a possible connection to robotics, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics).
